President Uhuru Kenyatta on Friday appointed a selection panel for the recruitment of the Director of Public Prosecutions. The appointments were made through a gazette notice dated February 2, 2018. Members of the panel include; Kennedy Kihara, Halakhe Waqo, Elizabeth Muli, Kagwiria Mbogori, Maryann Njau, and Francis Atwoli. The new DPP will replace Keriako Tobiko who is a now the CS nominee for Environment. Read: Uhuru tricked Tobiko into Cabinet job - Mutahi Ngunyi On January 5, President Uhuru appointed John Munyes, Ukur Yattani and former DPP Keriako Tobiko to the Cabinet.  Click here for the latest political news